I resolved to make my own art of her and somehow my imagination transmogrified her mere concept into - at least what I percieved to be - a living, breathing character that I could conjure willingly whenever. She was petite, a bit shorter than I was, though nevertheless maintaining a noble sturdiness I had come to admire in wolves. Most of the time, she wore a cute sundress and a sunhat. A glistening pelt of (mostly) gray and black fur undergirded her modest attire, poofing out at her collar like in the art I'd seen and replicated. A few other times she'd wear something more formal, like if we were dancing. It all depended on the context. I'd play out her existence either from my own perspective or through my self-insert lego character if my parents were watching. It's hard to remember what we ever specifically did together, but as far as I recall it was mostly just casual interaction to keep me company whenever I was cooped up and alone in my room. Thankfully, I was never caught. This lasted for a good couple years or so, but as I began to adjust to my new home and school she eventually just.. dissipated from my life. It's been such a long time that I don't even remember her name now. For some reason, I can't help but miss her.
